 so, you came to the right place. With the right forms plugin and the proper know-how, you can quickly and easily add password protection to your WordPress forms. In this article, weâ€™ll share how to secure your WordPress forms with password protection the EASY [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/secure-wordpress-forms-password-protection/\">How to Secure Your WordPress Forms with Password Protection</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12528:\"<p>Wondering how to secure your WordPress forms with password protection? If so, you came to the right place. With the right forms plugin and the proper know-how, you can quickly and easily add password protection to your WordPress forms.</p>\n<p>In this article, weâ€™ll share how to secure your WordPress forms with password protection the EASY way.</p>\n<h3>Password Protect Your Form with WPForms</h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wpforms.png\" alt=\"WPForms\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218485\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wpforms.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wpforms-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wpforms-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>If youâ€™re going to have forms on your <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/\">WordPress website</a>, then we recommend using the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-contact-form-plugins/\">absolute best forms plugin</a> on the market: <a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n<p>If youâ€™re asking about how to secure your WordPress forms with password protection, youâ€™re probably looking to avoid getting unwanted form submissions. If thatâ€™s the case, then <a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a> is the perfect choice for you.</p>\n<p>Not only does <a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a> have a Post Submissions addon, which will allow you to get submissions in the first place; itâ€™s also incredibly easy to add password protection to.</p>\n<p>Adding password protection to your <a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a> submission forms will save you from wasting time reviewing content you donâ€™t intend to use. Only those with access will be able to send you content.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a> features an intuitive drag and drop builder, making it easy to use and beginner-friendly, even when creating advanced forms. It comes with GDPR enhancements so that you can be compliant, even when asking for othersâ€™ valuable information.</p>\n<p>IsItWP readers can save 10 percent off the cost of WPForms Pro by using the coupon code <strong>SAVE10</strong>.</p>\n<p>Once youâ€™ve purchased the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\">WPForms</a> plugin, follow our 4-step guide below on how to secure your WordPress forms with password protection.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install WPForms on Your Website</h3>\n<p>From your WordPress dashboard, scroll down to Plugins on the left-hand side. Click the Add New button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/add-new-plugin.png\" alt=\"add new plugin\" width=\"775\" height=\"235\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223559\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/add-new-plugin.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/add-new-plugin-300x91.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/add-new-plugin-768x233.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>From there, click the <strong>Upload Plugin</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/upload-new-plugin.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"775\" height=\"222\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223560\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/upload-new-plugin.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/upload-new-plugin-300x86.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/upload-new-plugin-768x220.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Upload the .zip file you downloaded from the WPForms website. Note: If you havenâ€™t downloaded your plugin and addons from WPForms, you can find them in your Account section on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\">their website</a>.</p>\n<p>Once the plugin has been uploaded, click the <strong>Activate</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/activate-wpforms-plugin.png\" alt=\"activate WPForms plugin\" width=\"775\" height=\"331\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223561\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/activate-wpforms-plugin.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/activate-wpforms-plugin-300x128.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/activate-wpforms-plugin-768x328.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, go to the newly-added WPForms tab on your dashboardâ€™s navigation bar. Head to <strong>WPForms Â» Settings</strong>.</p>\n<p>Enter your license key in the appropriate field to gain access to all of WPForms Proâ€™s features. You can find your license key in your Account section on the WPForms website. Simply copy and paste it into the field.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/wpforms-license-key.png\" alt=\"WPForms license key\" width=\"775\" height=\"308\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223562\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/wpforms-license-key.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/wpforms-license-key-300x119.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/wpforms-license-key-768x305.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Your plugin is now ready to rock and roll. You have basic form-building capabilities.</p>\n<p>Now, itâ€™s time to kick it up a notch.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Activate Your Addons</h3>\n<p>There&#8217;re 2 addons youâ€™ll need to activate: <strong>Post Submissions</strong> and <strong>Form Locker</strong>. The first will allow you to accept content submissions from your visitors, while the second is needed to secure your form.</p>\n<p>First, head to <strong>WPForms Â» Addons</strong>.</p>\n<p>Locate the <strong>Post Submissions</strong> and <strong>Form Locker</strong> addons and install them by clicking the Install button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/install-addon.png\" alt=\"install addon\" width=\"775\" height=\"307\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223563\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/install-addon.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/install-addon-300x119.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/install-addon-768x304.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Once installed, make sure the addons are activated. Hit the activation toggle.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/activate-addon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"379\" height=\"302\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223564\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/activate-addon.png 379w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/activate-addon-300x239.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 379px) 100vw, 379px\" /></p>\n<p>It will turn green and say â€œActiveâ€� if youâ€™ve successfully activated it.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/active-status.png\" alt=\"active status\" width=\"369\" height=\"294\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223565\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/active-status.png 369w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/active-status-300x239.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 369px) 100vw, 369px\" /></p>\n<p>Youâ€™re good to go! Itâ€™s time to build your first form.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Create a WordPress Form</h3>\n<p>On your dashboard, head to <strong>WPForms Â» Add New</strong>.</p>\n<p>Once the WPForms editor appears, scroll down and find the <strong>Blog Submissions Form</strong> template and click on it.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/create-submission-form.png\" alt=\"create submission form\" width=\"773\" height=\"317\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223566\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/create-submission-form.png 773w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/create-submission-form-300x123.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/create-submission-form-768x315.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 773px) 100vw, 773px\" /></p>\n<p>A form for accepting blog posts will appear:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/modify-submission-form.png\" alt=\"modify submission form\" width=\"775\" height=\"325\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223567\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/modify-submission-form.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/modify-submission-form-300x126.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/modify-submission-form-768x322.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>Feel free to drag and drop fields to your heartâ€™s content. Get it looking exactly how you need it to, and then click <strong>Save</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Step 4: Enable Password Protection</h3>\n<p>To enable password protection on your submissions form, youâ€™ll be utilizing the Form Locker addon you activated.</p>\n<p>While still in the form editor, go toÂ <strong>SettingsÂ Â»Â Form Locker</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/form-locker-settings.png\" alt=\"form locker settings\" width=\"562\" height=\"359\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223568\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/form-locker-settings.png 562w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/form-locker-settings-300x192.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Check theÂ <strong>Enable Password Protection</strong>Â box under theÂ PasswordÂ section.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/form-locker-password-protection.png\" alt=\"form locker password protection\" width=\"562\" height=\"333\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223570\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/form-locker-password-protection.png 562w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/form-locker-password-protection-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>From there, you can configure the 2 password settings that appear. For <strong>Password</strong>, you can choose the password you want users to enter to access your submissions form. For <strong>Display Message</strong>, type what you want to appear above the password field so your users know they need a password in order to submit their content.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/password-settings.png\" alt=\"password settings\" width=\"562\" height=\"355\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223569\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/password-settings.png 562w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/password-settings-300x190.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Upon finishing, slick <strong>Save</strong>.</p>\n<p>Once your form is live on your site, this message (or whatever you wrote) will appear for your users:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/final-password-protected-form.png\" alt=\"final password protected form\" width=\"562\" height=\"235\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-223571\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/final-password-protected-form.png 562w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/final-password-protected-form-300x125.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>After the user enters the correct password, the submission form will appear and theyâ€™ll be able to send you their content.</p>\n<p>Your submission form is officially password protected!</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you learn how to secure your WordPress forms with password protection.</p>\n<p>If you liked this post, you might also love our tutorial on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/custom-user-registration-form-wordpress/\" title=\"How to Create a Custom User Registration Form in WordPress\">how to create a custom user registration form in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/secure-wordpress-forms-password-protection/\">How to Secure Your WordPress Forms with Password Protection</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://www.isitwp.com/secure-wordpress-forms-password-protection/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:28:\"https://www.isitwp.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";O:42:\"Requests_Utility_CaseInsensitiveDictionary\":1:{s:7:\"\0*\0data\";a:18:{s:6:\"server\";s:17:\"Sucuri/Cloudproxy\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Mon, 19 Nov 2018 18:18:41 GMT\";s:12:\"content-type\";s:34:\"application/rss+xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:11:\"x-sucuri-id\";s:5:\"14003\";s:23:\"content-security-policy\";s:26:\"upgrade-insecure-requests;\";s:16:\"x-xss-protection\";s:13:\"1; mode=block\";s:15:\"x-frame-options\";s:10:\"SAMEORIGIN\";s:22:\"x-content-type-options\";s:7:\"nosniff\";s:25:\"strict-transport-security\";a:2:{i:0;s:44:\"max-age=31536000; includeSubdomains; preload\";i:1;s:13:\"max-age=86400\";}s:10:\"set-cookie\";s:98:\"srv_id=9c4564d9ab24308e506a24325193b11c; expires=Mon, 19-Nov-18 12:46:26 GMT; max-age=3600; path=/\";s:4:\"vary\";s:6:\"Cookie\";s:7:\"expires\";s:29:\"Thu, 19 Nov 1981 08:52:00 GMT\";s:13:\"cache-control\";s:35:\"no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate\";s:6:\"prag